Dandu. Alt. 2500-3000'. Commiphora etc. scrub on red sandy soil derived from granite. Locally frequent. Northern Prov. Alt. 750 m., with mountain rising to 1100 m. Rainfall perhaps between 300 and 400 mm. with maxima in April and probably November. In 1952 the main rains started on 27th March. Rock red granite; soils: (a) a red sandy loam on well draines slopes, (b) pale sandy soil near watercourses, (c) a yellowish brown powdery soil on flats, (d) 'blackcotton soil', glutinous, cracking, in areas of impeded drainage. A rich Commiphora-Acacia scrub with scattered larger trees such as Delonix, Terminalia, Gyrocarpus.

Rock red granite; soils: - (a) a red sandy loam on well drained slopes, (b) pale sandy soil near watercourses, (c) a yellowish brown powdery soil on flats, (d) 'black cotton soil', glutinous, cracking, in areas of impeded drainage. Dandu, Northern Prov., Alt. 750 m., with mountain rising to 1100 m. Cracks in large granite rocks. Rainfall perhaps between 300 and 400 mm. with maxima in April and probably November. In 1952 the main rains started on 27th March. Rock red granite; soils:-(a) a red sandy loam on well drained slopes, (b) pale sandy soil near watercourses, (c) a yellowish brown powdery soil on flats, (d) 'black cotton soil', glutinous, cracking, in areas of impeded drainage. A rich Commiphora-Acacia scrub with scattered larger trees such as Delonix, Terminalia, Gyrocarpus.
